value.title: Kamala Harris receives first dose of Moderna Covid-19 vaccine on camera
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris is expected to receive the first dose of a Covid-19 vaccine on Tuesday, according to the Biden transition team.

value.title: Biden expected to call out Trump administration on pace of vaccine distribution
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is set to confront the slower-than-expected pace at which the Trump administration is administering coronavirus vaccines in remarks Tuesday afternoon, a transition official tells CNN.

value.title: Trump, Michelle Obama top Gallup's 2020 most admired lists
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump and former first lady Michelle Obama are the most admired man and woman of 2020, according to a new Gallup poll released Tuesday.

value.title: Russia, Afghanistan, Iraq: Joe Biden's foreign policy answers, through the years
value.excerpt: As a senator and vice president, Joe Biden spent his career developing relationships with foreign leaders. Meet the Press looks back at his answers to foreign policy questions over his decades-long career.

value.title: Walter Reed doctor who criticized Trump's hospital drive-by works last shift after being removed from schedule
value.excerpt: Dr. James Phillips, an emergency room doctor at Walter Reed National Military Medical Center, has been removed from his duty after publicly criticizing President Donald Trump's drive-by around the hospital after his coronavirus diagnosis.

value.title: Relief is coming: Trump backtracks and signs Covid aid into law
value.excerpt: The president's last-minute decision will restore enhanced unemployment assistance that expired Sunday and avert a shutdown that would have begun Tuesday.

value.title: Dancing pallbearers, the Mike Pence fly and pretty best friends: Here are the top memes of 2020
value.excerpt: "Since we can't see each other in person, using memes to kind of share feelings and connect with one another has become huge this year," said the editor of Know Your Meme.

value.title: Tennessee governor requests emergency declaration from President Donald Trump
value.excerpt: The "severity and magnitude" of the blast are more than state and local governments can handle, said Lee in a statement.

value.title: Americans suffer at Christmas while Trump golfs and sows chaos
value.excerpt: For Christmas this year, Washington is giving the country more pain.

value.title: Transition 2020: Biden allies push back on sweeping plan to promote fair housing
value.excerpt: Donald Trump scrapped an Obama-era rule on housing. Some local officials hope Joe Biden doesn’t simply restore it as is.

value.title: Here's what happens if Trump doesn't sign the $900 billion relief package
value.excerpt: Though Congress has passed a $900 billion Covid relief package, millions of Americans are in danger of losing important benefits just after the holidays if President Donald Trump continues to refuse to sign the bill.

value.title: The ‘Trump Bump’ for Books Has Been Significant. Can It Continue?
value.excerpt: As a new administration looms, publishers have snapped up another crop of forthcoming Trump books by prominent journalists and pundits.

value.title: California conservatives rebuke Trump pardon of Duncan Hunter
value.excerpt: Trump granted a full pardon Tuesday to Hunter, who was set to begin an 11-month sentence at a federal prison in two weeks after pleading guilty to stealing campaign funds for personal use.

value.title: Trump issues 26 new pardons, including ones for Stone, Manafort and Charles Kushner
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Wednesday evening announced 26 new pardons, including ones for longtime ally Roger Stone, former campaign chairman Paul Manafort and White House senior adviser Jared Kushner's father, Charles.

value.title: Congressional GOP grapples with 'unhinged' Trump
value.excerpt: Even in his waning days in power, President Donald Trump is still finding ways to inflict his signature loyalty tests on the Republican Party.

value.title: George Clooney on ‘The Midnight Sky’ and Donald Trump
value.excerpt: His new movie is on Netflix, but the actor-director says theaters won’t go away and Hollywood will be fine. He’s not so sure about Washington.

value.title: Biden chooses Connecticut education commissioner for top schools post
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden selected Connecticut Education Commissioner Miguel Cardona to be his Education secretary on Tuesday, adding another Latino to his roster of Cabinet appointees and choosing a leader who has pressed schools to remain open for in-person classes during the pandemic.

value.title: Biden team calls out Twitter over plan to wipe White House accounts' followers
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's transition team has pushed back against Twitter's decision to not allow the millions of followers of the White House Twitter accounts to be automatically retained when the accounts are handed over to the new administration.

value.title: Lev Parnas files motion to dismiss, says he was selectively prosecuted to protect Trump
value.excerpt: Lev Parnas, the indicted associate of Rudy Giuliani, has filed a motion to dismiss the campaign finance charges against him, arguing he has been selectively prosecuted and blocked from providing information to lawmakers seeking to impeach President Trump.

value.title: Biden: No 'obvious choice' yet for attorney general
value.excerpt: The president-elect also re-upped his commitment to not discuss his son's legal troubles with any AG candidates.

value.title: Biden says 'our darkest days' in battling Covid-19 'are ahead of us'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden will deliver remarks ahead of Christmas in Wilmington, Delaware, on Tuesday afternoon.

value.title: Newsom picks Alex Padilla to fill Kamala Harris' Senate seat
value.excerpt: Gov. Gavin Newsom appointed California Secretary of State Alex Padilla to fill Vice President-elect Kamala Harris' Senate seat on Tuesday, choosing the first Latino in state history for the role.

value.title: Televangelist Pat Robertson says Trump lives in an 'alternate reality' and should move on from election loss
value.excerpt: Televangelist Pat Robertson, a prominent conservative backer of Donald Trump, said Monday that the President is living in an "alternate reality" and should "move on" from his 2020 election loss.

value.title: From pivotal endorsement to Cabinet advice, Jim Clyburn is here for Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Don't call Rep. Jim Clyburn a member of President-elect Joe Biden's inner circle.

value.title: Trump issues executive order requiring 'beautiful' federal architecture
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump signed an executive order on Monday looking to ensure that federal buildings feature "beautiful" architecture, expressing a preference for classical architecture over modernist designs.

value.title: House conservatives strategize with Trump and Pence in push to challenge Biden's win
value.excerpt: Alabama GOP Rep. Mo Brooks and fellow House conservatives met privately on Monday with President Donald Trump and Vice President Mike Pence as the lawmakers prepared to mount a long-shot bid in January to overturn the Electoral College results that made Joe Biden the official winner of the election.

value.title: Biden looks to Susan Rice to elevate low-profile Domestic Policy Council
value.excerpt: "Susan will elevate and turbocharge a revitalized" council, Joe Biden said when he nominated the former national security adviser.

value.title: Trump discussed naming Sidney Powell special counsel during White House meeting
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump held a meeting at the White House on Friday evening in which he discussed the idea of naming appellate attorney Sidney Powell as a special counsel to investigate voter fraud in the election,

value.title: Romney: Trump has a 'blind spot' when it comes to Russia
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Mitt Romney said Sunday that President Donald Trump has a "blind spot" when it comes to dealing with Russia after the President downplayed a massive cyberattack on US federal agencies linked to the country, warning that the aggression "is a big wake up call for us."

value.title: The Trump survivors: Six Cabinet officials who stuck it out
value.excerpt: On Monday, Attorney General Bill Barr became the 12th of Donald Trump's Senate-confirmed Cabinet members either to resign or be fired by the President.
